parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause a loud grinding noise, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loud grinding noise from the rear end of the vehicle
especially when operating in all-wheel drive mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to lose power while driving, leading to a sudden stop and potential accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power while driving
especially at high speeds
resulting in the vehicle coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine and Catalytic Converter Pipe Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and catalytic converter pipe can cause the engine light to come on, leading to reduced engine performance and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine light comes on
abnormal feeling of engine power
and difficulty fixing the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the vehicle to emit loud noises and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Welding of the connection is bad
resulting in loud noises and potential exhaust system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer track can cause the vehicle to lose control and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Not specified
but stabilizer track issues can cause loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly shift into neutral or park, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle suddenly shifts into neutral or park
especially at high speeds
resulting in loss of control and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle moves unexpectedly
especially when starting or stopping
resulting in accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause injury from shattered glass, distraction, and loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Loud explosion
shattered glass
and sudden loss of sunroof integrity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected closure of the rear door can cause injury or trapping, especially for individuals with disabilities.
symptoms: The rear door starts to close unexpectedly while accessing the rear portion of the vehicle
and may not respond to manual intervention.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the remote start system can cause carbon monoxide accumulation in enclosed spaces, leading to potential health risks.
symptoms: The vehicle starts remotely without the owner's intention
often without their knowledge
and may continue to run for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The broken rear sunroof clip can cause the sunroof to remain open, leading to water ingress, noise, and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The rear sunroof remains open due to a broken clip
and the part is no longer available for replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan motor assembly can cause the 70-amp fuse to blow, leading to overheating and potential engine damage.
symptoms: The cooling fan motor assembly shorts out internally
blowing the 70-amp fuse dedicated to that circuit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of the passenger-side seat airbag can cause injuries, including burns, and potentially lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The airbag explodes and catches fire
causing injuries to occupants
and the airbag light may have previously illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short in Aux Outlet and Factory-Installed DVD Players
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical short can cause devices plugged into the aux outlet to malfunction or reset, and factory-installed DVD players to turn off, which can be a distraction to the driver and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Devices plugged into the aux outlet short out and reset
and factory-installed DVD players turn off when a door is opened or closed while the engine is running.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Evaporative Emission Canister Purge Solenoid Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporative emission canister purge solenoid valve can cause the vehicle to stall, especially after refueling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after refueling
the engine flutters and completely stalls
the vehicle goes into neutral
multiple restarts are required
the check engine light is on
and a loud noise is heard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain seal can cause oil leaks, which can lead to major engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the timing chain area
camshaft pitting
and engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk into a lower gear, and become stuck in a gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine loses power
the vehicle jerks into a lower gear
the vehicle becomes stuck in a gear
the engine strains and revs at unsafe levels
the transmission slips when shifting gears
and the check engine light is on.
